The paper deals with digital photo provenance and forensic analysis, which are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of neural imaging pipelines and optimization techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The need for reliable provenance analysis also implies a concern for security and cryptography (cs.CR).
